 El-Rufai. Photo: TWITTER/GOVKADUNA  The Commissioner for Internal Security and Home Affairs, Mr Samuel Aruwan, made the disclosure in a statement issued on Wednesday in Kaduna. According to him, heads of security agencies have been notified of the development. In the meantime, vigorous patrols and security surveillance will continue. Aruwan reiterated that the Kaduna State Government and security agencies will not condone acts that may lead to a breakdown of law and order, under any guise. He encouraged citizens to go about their lawful activities and to report any observed threats, suspicious movements, and security breaches to the Kaduna State Security.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .